description: Oh, brother (or sister)! Family sure can be a handful -- especially if you're talking about your sibling! You may argue, fight, and drive each other crazy, but for better or worse, you're stuck with 'em! Betty, Polly and their brother Chic all get along now, but did they always? Jughead's baby sister Jellybean is cute as a button, but sure can be tough to babysit! And what other Riverdale residents have siblings you may not have met yet? Join in on some fraternal fun with Archie and the gang as they celebrate one of the closest bonds around -- a brother or sister!

Cover: Edmund Bagwell (2000AD character montage)

  • Judge Dredd - Mega-City Confidential (part 1) (John Wagner - Colin MacNeil)
  • Slaine - The Brutania Chronicles: A Simple Killing (part 1) (Pat Mills - Simon Davis)
  • Outlier (part 1) (T.C.Eglington - Karl Richardson)
  • Sinister Dexter - The Generican Dream: Gun Shy (part 1) (Dan Abnett - Cam Smith 'Smudge')
  • Jaegir - Strigoi (part 1) (Gordon Rennie - Simon Coleby)

description: This month, we take a break from the misadventures of Knuckles, El Ravager, Zayre and Teflon Billy to focus instead on the Black Hands – Rasputin, Kragin, Mephisto and Fire Blossom – in their first full KoDT: Illustrated appearance! The barbarian, Kragin, is looking for a well-known group of adventurers to join up with – but first he’ll have to pass ‘The Test.’ Don’t miss this hysterical issue, entitled “Enter the Black Hands”!

description: Join the misadventures of Knuckles, El Ravager, Zayre and Teflon Billy as they wreak havoc with their unique brand of heroics. Turned evil by a cursed ring, the beautiful barbarian Zayre sets in motion the first stage of her plan to rule the world! Can her comrades, El Ravager, Knuckles and Teflon Billy, find a way to stop the most dangerous opponent they’ve ever faced – or will they even notice? Don’t miss the penultimate issue of the most surprising storyline ever, in “Enemy Mine.”

description:
Cartoonist, screenwriter and playwright Jules Feiffer's long out-of-print classic, "Tantrum", returns in this Fantagraphic edition, featuring new covers by Feiffer and an introduction by acclaimed Sandman creator Neil Gaiman.

The story of suburban disenchantment, "Tantrum" is the story of respectable and responsible businessman, Leo Quog, who, in the throes of a mid-life crisis, willfully regresses to the age of two. Having been two before, Leo demands his rights as a toddler: cuddling, cooing, tummy rubbing, and, most importantly, piggyback rides. In Leo's case, youth is definitely not wasted on the young. Feiffer has the uncanny ability to capture the frustrations of everyday life, while showing the lengths we'll go to escape from it.
name: TPB
